      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SHAZZA LOVE (1) added to a string of top-two finishes when she came from the back row to miss by a nose at Terang on Saturday. Was also off the second line when she scored easily two back at Ballarat. Should get every chance from the ace draw. THE GOLDEN HOOK (8) has improved with each start this time, delivering a win by 1.1 metres from this row at this venue last week. Should enjoy a pretty soft run from this draw and the sprint lane is in play so can go right on with the job. BREATHE EASY (3) didn't do a bad job when he drew poorly and raced last time out. Recorded a string of wins and placings prior and is better served by this barrier. LORIMERMAJOR (6) is worth some thought after his last-start fourth at Kilmore, beaten 3.2m.",
